caption: A+. Amazing. Great food, better service. The ratatouille and ham and cheese stand out, but nothing was not good. Meant to take pictures when the food came but it was too good so this is what's left.
Overall excellent empanadas, although I’m partial to the goat cheese, bacon & fig as well as the Malbec beef!

The empanadas are smaller than I expected but they were very tasty! The interior design was very cool and relaxed. And the service was quick (no line, polite and speedy server). I'll have to update my review when I try more if their options, but I'll definitely be back.
The ratatouille empanadas are fantastic, seasoned to perfection. The coffee they offer is metric coffee (which is also a very good quality brand) and the service is great!
The food is ok not great. The people they were really nice though

I wandered into 5411 Empanadas on accident after an Uber crisis one freezing night last week. Manny was so sweet, took such great care of me, even gave me tea to warm up. I didn't order any food that night but his kindness & hospitality made me want to come back to try it the next day - I was certainly not disappointed. The empanadas are perfectly portion sized and extremely flavorful. And they have so many variety. My favorites were the spinach/onion and also the barbecue chicken. The next time I go back I plan to get the bacon/date/goat cheese. This is my first time ever having an empanada and I easily ordered four or five! I will definitely be back. Thank you Manny!! :) You are proof that there are still cool people in the world.
Tasty but small.
Amazing empanadas!!! I especially enjoyed the mac and cheese one...and the green dipping sauce was delightful. 💥
Delicious and easy to hold. Prepared quickly when you're on-the-go.
Excellent

I drive an hour and a half to get these empanadas. I've been told these are like authentic argentine empanadas and I can't get enough of them. People I know who are from Argentina say these make them feel at home.
Great place and staff. A huge variety of empanadas and very tasteful.
(Translated by Google) Excessive waiting time for 3 meat patties.  (Original) Excesivo tiempo de espera para 3 empanadas de carne.
Even had a empanada before. I'm happy I trying them for my maiden voyage. Never looking back again

Decent empanadas with numerous options to choose from.  Both sauces were good.  The frozen bake and home option was not very successful on our side - I think we got the over temp wrong as they were a bit gummy.  But they were yummy!  But overall if you are looking for a quick snack and in the areas worth stopping by.

The empanadas are always great. I recommend trying the Bacon Dates & Goat Cheese empanada - amazing! I also really enjoy Malbec Beef and Mac & Cheese.  The outdoor music was pretty annoying the last time I went there, because the speaker's treble was too loud and it made songs unpleasantly sharp.  Highly recommended for lunch!
Excellent food, creative menu.
My fiancé and I come here all the time and it never disappoints. Our favorite is the spinach and cheese with the Chimichurri sauce 🤤 I can’t recommend this place enough!
Excellent place for tasty Argentinian food. I love it here. Reminds me of a place in New York I loved to visit.
Delicious and a great value too. Wow.
argentinian food... so great. Looking forward to a return trip. This place has a nice feel to it.
Great empanadas. I recommend the malbec beef!
Unique, delicious and affordable.  Fun setting with outdoor seating.  Empanadas only $2.99 each...plus a great selection of coffee and teas.
Food was amazing! Be sure to get the sauce with the empanadas. Service was great too
Delicious food. Great patio seating.

This place is absolutely delicious! We got 4 empanadas to share between the two of us, and it was the perfect amount for lunch. Their chai latte is also delicious. Friendly staff, and a really cute spot. Great outdoor seating in a little nook, and great COVID spacing for seating. Happy to call this our new go-to empanadas place!
Argentinian food, mmm, my favorite treat. Visited on a Thursday. Nothing but enjoyable experiences here. The bill was decent. Similar to a cafe in Las Vegas I liked.
Amazing food, vibe and most importantly the service is outstanding.  Feels like home away from home
Great first time experience. Amazing taste
Good place for tasty argentinian food. food was so delish. this place has a great feel to it. atmosphere and food reminds me of virginia beach.
A top spot for quality Argentinian food. One of the best spots in the area. Looking forward to returning with my relatives. Menu is like a place in San Francisco I loved.
Argentinian food at this spot - very good. Service is typically above par. This place has a nice design. Makes me feel like I am back in Sacramento.
Absolutely great selection and quality of food

argentinian food and the atmosphere here is great. I love this place, great food & service. The staff was very welcoming and observant. Prices are reasonable I would say. This place has great reviews for a reason.
Great empanadas, good service.  Priced well.

Great selecting, service and most importantly empanadas! I've been coming here for several years and love their large selection. I also highly recommend getting some frozen ones to take home and make when you want. A little egg wash and in the air fryer they go!

Best empanadas in Chicago - great selection and variety of flavors. Good range of vegetarian empanadas, too! The bacon, date and goat cheese is incredible - must try. And don’t forget your side of chimichurri.
Came in for a to go order. Really sweet and personable staff. Provided water for us on the way out into the hot summer air. Will definitely return. Oh! And the empanadas are awesome!

Omg... Was at a vet in Buffalo Grove and their food truck was there. Was av little hungry while waiting so decided to give them a try. I'm so glad I did!! Absolutely amazing. The bacon dates and goat cheese was heaven in my mouth... The other three were all good but I'm glad the bacon dates and goat cheese one was the last one in ate... All I can say is yummmmmmm...  You should definitely give them a try!!!
Great taste, service and value.   Malbec beef and chorizo empanadas highly recommended.  Great coffee too.
I love this place, great snacks and peaceful patio.
Had them for the first time and wasn't disappointed very good and my favorite is the mushroom thyme and blue cheese so far
Empanadas are really tasty and I giving two sta because they are really tiny I guess the price but y can pay 6 or 10 dollars each BUT BIGGER
This place rules
(Translated by Google) Delicious, fresh empanadas!  (Original) Riquísimas empanadas, frescas !
Great authentic Argentinian empanadas.
The bacon, dates and goat cheese one and Merlot Beef were amazing!!
So many great flavors and cooked fresh. The prices can be a bit whack so it’s hard to get full, but they’re so good
Was wonderful to stop in for a cappuccino and to split empanadas with friends. Great spot!
Great supper food
Nice little chill spot, not too expensive & the Empanadas where really good. I wanted more.
Great food and such a creative and well executed variety of fillings. Never disappointed. I usually order them in and make a selection of chutneys to go with them
$3 for tiny empanadas is a lot , also the taste was not best !
(Translated by Google) The super bad attention !! The person who served me the super rude cashier  (Original) La atencion super mala!! La persona que me atendió el cajero super grosero
I don't care for all the empanadas, but most are solid and a few, like the Malbec beef, are fantastic.
Excellent Empanadas. Tried 2 veggie ones and 2 meat. All were fantasteic!!!!
Excellent service and tasty empanadas. The ambience it’s really nice and clean. I little bit pricey for the size of the empanadas.
Empanadas were delicious staff was friendly
Stopped in to try some empanadas today and they were outstanding! I had the chicken curry and the bacon cheddar egg, and then one of the alfajores cookies!! Amazing
Good empanadas..!
Nice empanadas! Tried the beef, date & bacon, purple potato, and sweet corns. Would absolutely recommend.
Friendly service and tasty food.
Very cute and clean place! I only tried the turmeric latte so I cant say anything for the food items but I really enjoyed my latte!
Unique and delicious flavors, the empanadas were hot and fresh, but a bit pricey
The empanadas are amazing here!
They have great food and fast deliveries

Excellent spot for inexpensive and flavorful empanadas. Their most popular Malbec beef is number one for a reason— definitely try it out! I also had bacon, dates, and goat cheese empanada, as well as the curry chicken. All were delicious, and you can’t beat the price.
Good service and great food.  Make sure you try the bacon and dates. My personal favorite

So glad we decided to pop into this Empanada spot. Really appreciated the outdoor seating options on a beautiful afternoon. The food was fantastic. The Malbec Beef, Chicken Curry, and Mac & Cheese empanadas were all delicious, and the side sauces only added to the experience. The staff was extremely friendly and supportive, provided great input!
Yummy, and friendly service!
Very delicious empanadas! 😋
argentinian food at this place - very tasty. Service is always awesome even when they have a full house. Nothing but pleasant experiences here. Food is similar to a cafe in Portland I loved.

It was my first time to try Argentinian food, it’s good, Nice place. I enjoyed the music there,I like spinach & cheese and mushroom one the most I will come soon to try the desserts  I just hope they served the coffee and tea with a cup, not in the paper one .

I ordered a beef, chicken BBQ and a Ratatouille. The beef and Ratatouille (veggie) were fine. The chicken made my child - who LOVES empanadas - make go 🤢 (yuuuuck).  Called to explain my teen's reaction and ask if I can get a beef instead and they said no, that I'd have to just buy another. For $4, there is no way. Look how small they are! We are questioning if this is authentic Latin American because the taste does not lead us to believe so - authentic Latin American empanadas as delicious; these were edible. I will not be back.
Love this place. Empanadas are baked, not fried which means no greese on the outside and your clothes don't stink after eating here.  It is a small space, but we've always been able to get a seat.
Nice place delicious too
Amazing food with a lot of interesting options.
A fav location for delicious Argentinian food. Service is prompt even when they are busy. The staff was very friendly and kind. This place has a cool design.
Try chicken curry for sure
Always perfect
Good food but terrible customer/ delivery service!!! So disappointed

I was skeptical going into this because I don’t usually see empanadas as a good choice for dinner. I was pleasantly surprised. The food was delicious. The craft beer was incredible. I would recommend it to anybody!
No parking spots around
Great!
So many flavor options. We tried 4 different one and had a hard time deciding on a favorite. The sweet onion was amazing. Can wait to come back and try some more.
Great price and the empanadas are not greasy at all!

Empanadas were well-made and delicious. They were made to have structure and add texture. I liked the Chimichuri dipping sauce my sister went back for and the dessert empanadas were so good I didn't get one.
Adorable deliciousness !!!
Good selection, could include more fish options

Great experience ordering and quick food service. I say you need three empanadas and the chimichurri sauce if you like Spicy.  There is no bad empanada.  I really liked the new 🐔 curry empanada and the 🍌 Nutella one.  Thanks for the tasty treats!
Delicious! I love the fig and goat cheese one.
First time here. Tried many different empanadas. They were all amazing! What a cool little unique place. Love it! Will be back again.
Love, love the empanadas here! They're unique in flavors and are simply delicious. The coffee is great too. Highly recommended the chai tea!

Every empanada I've had here is incredible and I am on a mission to try them all. This last time I had a mushroom thyme and it was actually one of the most memorable so far! Definitely give this place a try 👌

This place never disappoints! A great selection of about 20 baked empanadas with something for everyone. Definitely spend the extra 50 cents for the chimichurra sauce! This visit was mushroom and goat cheese and a delicious sweet/savory bacon/date.
Great place to pop into for a quick bite.  My wife and I each tried a couple different recipes, each better than the last.  Very clean, great service, priced right.  Recommend.
Love the small place! The best empanadas I've tried. Best choice the date, bacon and goat cheese.
Amazing

Yummm so tasty and nice and quiet and laid back. You could go there to work or hang out with a friend and catch up. Not usually a wait unless it’s summer and you want to sit out on the porch. I recommend trying the bacon date and goat cheese - it’s my fav

The ambience is so cute and quaint. The service is awesome you just buy and sit and eat.  The empanadas are yummy too if you like them baked and soft. Chimichurri sauce is a must. My fav was the one with goat cheese and bacon surprisingly, since it was sort of sweet but flavorful.

This place is great. My grandma makes great empanadas so I've got a high standard for empanadas and this met it. Definitely making the trip here again some time soon. I tried the Malbec beef, curry chicken, bacon dates and goat cheese, sweet corn, spinach and cheese, and caramelized onion. Each and Every one of them was great. Fun fact/story. They accidentally made a duplicate order of 3 of them and brought them out. I told them of the mistake but they let us keep the extra empanadas. Great food and atmosphere.
It's alright.... I've had way better... Lito's empanadas 5 mins away

Cute little place with some great enpanadas and great service! I think the mac and cheese was one of my favorites after it was recommended by the girl.  They also had dessert empandas so my friend got the nutella and banana one. He seemed to really like it. Wish I had pictures to upload but I ate them too fast🤣

I didn’t get to try the food or even deliver the food I was contracted to pickup. They EXPECTED A DELIVERY DRIVER TO WAIT IN LINE FOR FOOD THATS PREPARED and ordered online, shows they don’t properly hold and store perishable food. It also shows delivery customers are second class citizens like the drivers who deliver food. Skip it. Even McDonalds processes drivers in and out faster.
Best empanadas in town. I don't like that they don't have anymore the potato chorizo but my favorite is bacon dates and goat cheese.
Quaint & tasty.
Do yourself a favor and get the Malbec beef! Convienent location for everyone who lives in Lakeview. There has never been a line all the times I have gone.

Ordered 2 empanadas today and they gave us the new chicken curry to try for free! The wait time was like 10 minutes. The ratatouille tasted amazing, and is my all time favorite. The malbec beef was good but no wow factor. Surprisingly, chicken curry had a lot of flavor but was a little on the dry side. I love that there are quite a few tables for outdoor seating. Would definitely recommend to stop by and try a few. They also have those stamp cards where you get a stamp if you buy 3 and after 10 stamps, you get 3 free empanadas.

Love the food here! First time trying empanadas and they were delicious. Highly recommend this little resturant. It was very clean. I like the indoor and outdoor seating areas. The food came out fairly fast and the employees were very nice.
2 stars, only because the food was okay. The atmosphere and wait time were absolutely miserable. The food was not too bad, but not good enough to return and deal with the atmosphere
Simply my favorite stop in my two-day trip to Chicago.  So good I went twice!  Looking forward to my next trip so I can go again. :)

This is one of, if not the smallest of all of the 5411 locations. The emanadas are as good as always, but the space is limited. Might want to visit a different spot during a cold thay or take it to go. But in the end, you can't go wrong with 5411 Empanadas...
Cozy venue with friendly staff and delicious food. A variety of flavors with unique flare. Definitely check this place out!

I didn't have any expectations walking in, but the empanadas far exceeded any expectations I could have had.  The food was beyond delicious, the service was fast, and incredibly friendly.  I'm looking forward to returning and spending more time in the restaurant and taking advantage of the outdoor seating area.
Fast, friendly, and affordable. Very interesting choices. Each I tried was tasty.
The bacon, dates and goat cheese empanada was absolutely fantastic. The crust on all of the ones we tried was perfect.
Great for a quick and delicious bite. You can choose any of the empanada options they have in a mix and match style. Friendly staff, clean space, definitely recommend.
Kinda small for my liking and the price. The bacon date empanada was very good though!
The empañadas are ok, but definitely a gentrified version of the real stuff.
Great empanadas and very friendly service.
Excellent empanadas, definitely coming back.
The empanadas were delicious. If you're hungry, you'll need at least three to fill you up. Friendly service.
yummy to my tummy
I love this place! Tiny and delicious empanadas, but much more substantial then they look. Chimichuri sauce is my s#*t!
Very fresh
Amazing

No venden bebidas "saludables", solo sodas.... y si pides salsa o Chimichurri, TE COBRAN POR ESO, realmente absurdo. El peor lugar que he visitado en Chicago
Great place for a quick snack. In the summer, they have a nice patio you can hangout on. It's BYOB so grab a bottle of wine and have a few empanadas.
The empanadas are fresh and tasty and the atmosphere is super chill. I got the corizo bean and egg, and BBQ chicken with the two sauces they offer. Do yourself a favor and try all the flavors.
Good affordable food with plenty of variety

Their food is very good but lately their service has been kinda bad, I don't feel like I can ask anything without getting an attitude. I might come in if I see certain employees aren't there but otherwise I'd rather forego my morning empanadas for the time being.
Nice pies
Excellent flavors and ingredients; low prices; superb service; nice balance between rustic and modern decor.

It's a cute place for a light lunch.  The flavors are lovely but I can't get past how much the food costs for what you get.  I have a decently healthy appetite, and for $12 their empanadas just don't cut it.  I'd estimate the each one is roughly 2x3 inches.  A favorite is their goat cheese and date.  Probably best for a light lunch or cute afternoon date.
great empanadas
Great empanadas.
Incredible!! Had beef empanadas along with ham and cheese. Was so good considering going back tomorrow:)
Small empanadas big taste had 3 tasty will came back
My favorite place to eat when I lived in Lakeview
Good empanadas, not the best I have tried in a Chicago; but good enough. The chimichurri sauce is a little bland. The chorizo empanada is good, I recommend it.
The Beef and Chorizo and Papas are the best!!
This cute counter service empanada joint is amazing. Everything is made to order and the staff is really nice too. Love the outdoor space it has to offer!
This is a cute little place with plenty of options. My girlfriend and I split a bunch of different items off the menu and were pleased with them all!

At $2.75 a pop, these tiny empanadas are not cheap. But delicious and quality stuff, they are. From order to your hands, expect at least 10 minutes as they bake them right when you put your order in. I regret not getting a groupon for them when it was offered. These things are delicious but not affordable enough for me to enjoy as often as I would like to.  Things to note -Sauces cost extra, .50 cents to be exact. 1 sauce could cover 3-4 empanadas -No minimum for cards

Delicious empanadas. I got the malbec beef empanada and the inside was tender and juicy and the outside was crispy and chewy but not too deep fried. Price was a bit on the high end given its smaller size but it's a nice place to drop by for a small bite.
Try them all!
Empanadas. They're good. Not much else.

This cute little store front is home to some of the most amazing flavor combinations one can fit into a crust filled pouch. They also have some nice coffees you can enjoy there or take it with you. A comfy patio completes the ambiance.
Nice outdoor seating (not  ton of space inside though). Fantastic empanadas, both veggie and meat based.
Yummy empanadas! Had he veggie and egg empanadas.. cheap and yummy!
Awesome food, lovely people, you won't be disappointed!
Idk. I try to like it but they just don't taste that good.
Favorite Empandas. Always fresh. Customer service is on point. Jr  at the front was awesome
Great empanadas! Chorizo and potato was great. Had a few and not one in the bunch was bad.
The most unique style of food I've tried. Delicious too. Take a friend and treat yourselves to something new and fresh!
Good place for a small bite to eat. They serve Argentine styled empanadas
Nice place. Food is great. The employee that helped me was straight out of stoner 1973. "Totally radical, dude!". He was fun.
Reminds me of my Bolivian empanadas. Yum! Miss seeing their food truck by the AON building, though.
Tasty empanadas!
Not the most cozy or enchanting atmosphere, but you can't argue the quality of the food. Good for vegetarians or meat lovers. We nearly had one of each between the two of us.
Great empanadas! Had the beef-dates-goat cheese, the bacon-cheddar-egg and the sweet corn. Liked the mexican fanta!;)
Cool vibe, good inexpensive food. 'Holiday Jones' in the back, pretty cool.
Great nook with very tasty empanadas.
My favorite place. Always good
Super good empanadas! Glad I checked this place out.
My husband and I have been going here for years! It's an absolute must - the food is great, the atmosphere is chill, and overall have never been disappointed
Yum! careful, they're hot when they come out.
Good empanadas with a hip interior. Check out groupon for deals!
Ham and cheese may sound like the boring choice, but god damn is it good! Love this place, really can't go wrong.
The bacon, date, and goat cheese is perfectly sweet and salty. It's my favorite, hands down.
Awesome empanadas! The goat cheese, bacon and date ones are tasty. Same with the Malbec beef. Employees are super friendly and don't spit in your food as far as I know
They have the best empanadas and chimichurri sauce that I have tasted in Chicago!
pretty delicious. a bit small inside though- great for takeout
The Malbec beef is my favorite.

While I haven't had any other types of Argentinian food, I can say that these empanadas are really well done. They've got fifteen different types of empanadas that are all very good. They run for about $2.50 and they're usually as wide as your middle finger and was large as your thumb, if that helps you visually.
Great people, great simple food.
Tasty, but way overpriced for how tiny they are.
Far from a good Argentinean empanada
This is one of those hidden gems in Lakeview that you must try!

I was having vacations in Chicago for Thanksgiving, I'm argentinian and I can tell these are not Argentinian Empanadas or the cook is not argentinian, where he learned to make empanadas?  1-The size is too small (like a wedding canapé) I measured one empanada and it was 1.5 inches long. 2-The price is too expensive for that size 3-The flavor is not the best, too salty. Beef empanadas need some ingredients. 4-The dough was not the right one. 5-The Chimichurri was fair 6-The service was good, the guy at the front was friendly and the place looks clean.
One of the best lunch spots in Chicago. I highly recommend the sweet corn empanada. Regardless of what you get, make sure to order the chimichurri.

Every time I visit I always go for the bacon dates & goat cheese or keep it simple with the ham & cheese. Either way you can't go wrong.  Wait times are almost always minimal. I don't think I've ever waited more than 5 minutes to start an order.  The place is usually has a couple people inside or out. They tend to be younger, recent graduate crowds that enjoy this place.
A great spot to have well prepared food. The breading is especially authentic.
The spinach empanada is my favorite.
Great experience, amazing empanadas and good service. Go here.
Amazing

The various empanada flavors will keep you wanting more! These delectable morals are baked with options ranging from sweet to savory. Great for catering large groups. Each empanada is distinguished by the crimp in the dough. Be sure to get the chimichurri dipping sauce...it's to die for!

A friend and I purchased a voucher online for one dozen. We tried the following flavors:  1) Bacon, date, and goat cheese 2) Sweet Corn 3) Malbec Beef 4) Beef 5) Ham & cheese 6) Ratatouille  BD&G is the best one and Corn is a close 2nd. It is a BYOB joint. The chairs look nice, but they're just hollow plastic. Brightly lit place. After you order, grab your own plates, flatware, and cups. Although I wasn't sure where to dispose of my trash when I was done with my meal, so I assumed the guy behind the counter took care of it?  I did try the ginger fresca and it was alright. Next time, I will try the chorizo & patatas and the spinach and cheese. MUST get the CHIMICHURRI sauce!
One could happily live of 5411 Empanadas forever. Sweet corn is my absolute favorite, and the chimichurri sauce is a must try. Small but mighty bites - I think just one is filling enough for lunch.
100% the best place for empanadas in the city.   They have a great patio for nice evenings out, and it's BYOB.  The staff is really cool too.  Go there... now!
Mediocre empanadas at high prices.  Very small portions.  I dont understand how this placw gets gos reviews
got three empanadas.  Mushroom and chorizo were weird as hell.  Bacon prune was the best thing I ever had.  Go and get two or three of those. I assure you, you'll be So happy. MMMM
Delicious, and you couldn't beat the price! Would recommend to anyone who wants to try something that's light yet filling!

I want to eat ALL the empanadas. I have a dream-day plan of going here with a few friends, ordering everything on the menu, and sharing. (So far, though, my fave is ham & cheese.) Vibe here is very simple, which fits the one-item menu.

The banana nutella is my favorite! I tend to take them to go but they do have a few tables for dining in. They really are heavenly. Well made with quality ingredients. Perfect crust on the outside. So many choices! I tend to favor their vegetarian filling empanadas just a bit more.  I like buying a few extra, they reheat very well.

So good. Sooooooo good. They have a great selection of fillings, including quite a bit of vegetarian ones. The spinach and the ratatouille are my favs, not including the dessert empanadas they also carry. The place is really tiny so if it's prime eating time I wouldn't expect to get a table there, but it's totally worth it! Plus, they have a food truck that roams around.
Everything I've tried here – the mushroom/blue cheese and ham/cheese – was wayyy too salty. I love the idea of this place and I really want to like it, but I haven't had a good experience yet.

5411 is the place to be for empanadas!  So many delicious options to chose from.  I would highly recommend the bacon, date & goat cheese, the caramelized onion and the sweet corn.  Such a cute little venue and you can BYOB and there is even outdoor seating in the warm weather days.

It's slap ya mama good. I’m thrilled to have had 5411 pop my Empanada cherry. Thanks to Google City Experts Community Managers for including them at the Threadless + Google event. The fig, bacon, goat cheese concoction sent shivers down my spine. Don’t sleep on 5411.
Bacon date and goat cheese was very tasty, will keep an eye out for the food truck in the future.
BBQ chicken is my choice. Could eat them all day. My daughter is the empanada pro and she enjoyed this place immensely. A nice change of pace.

Argentinian style empanadas. The bacon, date, and goat cheese empanadas are to die for! I've tried all of their empanadas but I always go back to this one. Very reasonably priced. Great for a quick lunch or dinner.

Always great,  and worth the few minutes. Fluffy crispy dough from hot air not oil.  Great braised flavors in a easy to hold package.   Wait 5 minutes before you indulge.  Burned tongues don't taste the love inside as well.

These empanadas as SO GOOD! These are not the empanadas you might be expecting so it's worth it to mention that these are Argentinian style which basically means they are like tiny delicious portable pies. They are reasonably prices at $2.50 each and freshly prepared to order so it takes about 8-10 mins to get them ready. My personal favorite is the Malbec Beef (it's basically pot roast) but the Onion and regular Beef, and BBQ Chicken, are also really good. I've never tried them myself but they also have sweet as well as savory for a nice desert. They had banana and nutella the last time I was there. They are relatively small so you'll need multiples and each type is folding differently so you can keep track of which is which before you dig in. My only complaint is that this place is so tiny. I actually went to Lincoln Park in search of this place and I still almost missed it, tucked away on Clark next to the mall. If their food truck hadn't been sitting outside at the time I totally would have walked right past it. It has kind of a cozy coffee shop vibe and there is only enough room for maybe 10 people to sit inside so recommend getting these to go. FYI they also serve "Mexican Coke" mean it comes in a bottle so grab one of those too.

Great spot in Lakeview, as it's small, modern and cozy. Perfect for lunch or a quick bite as you pay per empanada. Loved the Malbec beef, chicken BBQ and spinach and cheese empanadas. Would easily go back so I can try everything else! Glad to see plenty of vegetarian options on the menu as well.
These empanadas are Not Traditional. And that's not a bad thing. In fact, I happily welcome the gourmet flavors that are so compactly packaged. LOVE LOVE LOVE

Wonderful modern space right next to the Landmark cinema building in Lakeview.  They also have a nice patio.  But forget about the space -- the reason for visiting is certainly the fresh-out-of-the-oven Argentinian style empanadas.  Merlot beef is my favorite but I've also never had a bad one there.  Chimichurri is obligatory.
Not overly impressed with the bacon/date and lack of goat cheese empanada which was suggested as one of the most popular choices.
I had a caramelized onion empanada. It was very fresh and it tasted amazing! THey are well priced and worth every single penny. Strongly recommended.

These Empanadas are legit Argentine empanadas. My husband & I love coming here to have a little taste of authentic food. The most coolest part about this place is that they let you bring your own drinks in, we love bringing mate:)
Empandas Argentinas, expertly cooked. Really good flavors. I recommend trying any and all of them, and finish it off with a chocolate covered alfajor or banana and nutella empanda.

These are, by far, the best empanadas that I have ever had. They are authentic and incredible. The restaurant, itself, is great to go to with friends or on a date, it's BYOB, and quick (or you can stay long, too).
Solid design, upbeat atmosphere, quiet staff and good food
Best in Chicago. Every single one they serve is mouthwatering. I have cravings for the Dates & Bacon with Goat Cheese, ridiculously delicious!

This place is amazing. 5411 Empanadas started out as a food truck. The empanadas are Argentinian, so they are baked with gourmet fillings. Each costs $2.25 and come in bbq chicken; bacon, date, and walnut; sweet corn; banana nutella; and other awesome tastes. When you order, wait 10 minutes and then enjoy the heck out of these little hand pies.  This has become my go-to spot for a snack, lunch, or quick dinner. BYOB, too!

I don't know what it is, maybe my luck but I have yet to get an empanada that I enjoy. The decor is absolutely amazing. A simple design aesthetic ala Apple, unfortunately the food doesn't match up to it.
5411 is the best place for a quick lunch/dinner around Clark/Diversey. Can't beat $2.25 for a quality empanada.
Overall pretty good we had one of each, but the prices are a little high. I also would have liked to be greeted with a smile :)
Best empanadas in-town, make sure you try the malbec beef and the alfajores for dessert!
